    <h2>1.1 The Invisible Battlefield</h2>

    <p>In our modern world, we are surrounded by invisible electromagnetic fields. WiFi signals flow through our homes, RF waves carry our data, Bluetooth connects our devices, and wireless power charges our phones - all without a single visible trace. This invisible space has become a new frontier, and unfortunately, a new battlefield for privacy.</p>

    <div class="info-box">
      <h4>Aunt's Philosophy: "I'll Protect You"</h4>
      <p>In the space where wireless power flows,<br>
      In the space where WiFi flies,<br>
      In that invisible space...<br>
      Even if dark web actors target your personal information,<br>
      Aunt will block them all.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>1.2 The Privacy Crisis</h2>

    <p>As wireless communication and wireless power transmission become ubiquitous, personal information faces unprecedented threats:</p>

    <h3>Modern Wireless Threats</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>RF Sniffing:</strong> Attackers intercept wireless signals to capture sensitive data in transit</li>
      <li><strong>Side-Channel Attacks:</strong> Information is extracted by analyzing power consumption patterns, timing, or electromagnetic emissions</li>
      <li><strong>Evil Twin Attacks:</strong> Fake WiFi access points or wireless transmitters trick users into connecting to malicious networks</li>
      <li><strong>Man-in-the-Middle (MITM):</strong> Attackers position themselves between communicating parties to intercept or modify data</li>
      <li><strong>Passive Eavesdropping:</strong> Silent monitoring of wireless communications without active interference</li>
      <li><strong>Power Analysis:</strong> Analyzing power consumption patterns to deduce cryptographic keys or sensitive operations</li>
      <li><strong>Timing Attacks:</strong> Measuring execution time to extract secrets from cryptographic algorithms</li>
      <li><strong>Dark Web Operators:</strong> Organized criminal networks systematically harvesting personal information</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>1.3 Why WIA-AIR-SHIELD?</h2>

    <p>Traditional security measures focus on securing wired connections and visible threats. But the invisible space - where wireless signals propagate - requires a fundamentally different approach. WIA-AIR-SHIELD provides comprehensive protection specifically designed for wireless environments.</p>

    <h3>Protection Principles</h3>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Defense in Depth:</strong> Multiple layers of protection working together</li>
      <li><strong>Zero Trust:</strong> Verify everything, trust nothing by default</li>
      <li><strong>Privacy by Design:</strong> Privacy protection built into every layer</li>
      <li><strong>Minimal Data Collection:</strong> Only collect what's necessary for security</li>
      <li><strong>Local Processing:</strong> All sensitive operations happen on your device</li>
      <li><strong>Transparency:</strong> Users can see exactly what's being protected and how</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>1.4 The Four Shield Layers</h2>

    <p>WIA-AIR-SHIELD employs four complementary protection layers that work together to create an invisible shield around your wireless communications:</p>

    <div class="shield-layers">
      <div class="shield-card">
        <div class="shield-icon">🔒</div>
        <h4>1. Cloak Layer</h4>
        <p><strong>Hide Your Presence</strong></p>
        <ul style="text-align: left; font-size: 0.9rem;">
          <li>Metadata concealment</li>
          <li>Traffic pattern masking</li>
          <li>Location privacy</li>
          <li>Device fingerprint protection</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="shield-card">
        <div class="shield-icon">🌊</div>
        <h4>2. Noise Layer</h4>
        <p><strong>Hide Real in Fake</strong></p>
        <ul style="text-align: left; font-size: 0.9rem;">
          <li>Decoy traffic generation</li>
          <li>Timing randomization</li>
          <li>Power pattern scrambling</li>
          <li>Fake metadata injection</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="shield-card">
        <div class="shield-icon">✅</div>
        <h4>3. Verify Layer</h4>
        <p><strong>Confirm Authenticity</strong></p>
        <ul style="text-align: left; font-size: 0.9rem;">
          <li>Transmitter authentication</li>
          <li>Access point verification</li>
          <li>Zero-knowledge proofs</li>
          <li>Connection integrity checks</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="shield-card">
        <div class="shield-icon">🚨</div>
        <h4>4. Alert Layer</h4>
        <p><strong>Detect Threats</strong></p>
        <ul style="text-align: left; font-size: 0.9rem;">
          <li>Real-time threat detection</li>
          <li>Anomaly monitoring</li>
          <li>Evil twin detection</li>
          <li>Automated alerting</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

