    <h2>1.6 The WIA Family</h2>

    <p>WIA-AIR-SHIELD is the protective aunt in the WIA family of standards, working closely with other family members:</p>

    <div class="info-box">
      <h4>Family Members</h4>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Father (WIA-INTENT):</strong> "Express your intent" - Natural language interface for wireless systems</li>
        <li><strong>Mother (WIA-OMNI-API):</strong> "I'll embrace everything" - Universal API for all wireless protocols</li>
        <li><strong>Uncle (WIA-AIR-POWER):</strong> "I'll share power with you" 💪 - Wireless power transmission standard</li>
        <li><strong>Aunt (WIA-AIR-SHIELD):</strong> "I'll protect you" 🛡️ - Wireless privacy protection standard</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <p>Aunt works especially closely with Uncle (WIA-AIR-POWER) to ensure that wireless power transmission is not only convenient but also secure and private. When your device charges wirelessly, Aunt verifies the transmitter's authenticity and monitors for any suspicious activity.</p>

    <h2>1.7 Core Philosophy: Hongik Ingan</h2>

    <div class="info-box">
